properties.description: The People's Liberation Army Navy's (PLAN's) Shandong carrier strike group (CSG) arrived in Hong Kong Special Administrative Region in China. The CSG consisted of the Kuznetsov-class aircraft carrier CNS Shandong (pennant no. 17), Type 055 Renhai-class cruiser CNS Yan'an (pennant no. 106), Type 052D Luda-class destroyer CNS Zhanjiang (pennant no. 165) and Type 054A Jiangkai II-class frigate CNS Yuncheng (pennant no. 571). CNS Shandong and CNS Yan'an were docked at Hong Kong's Victoria Harbour while CNS Zhanjiang and CNS Yuncheng were docked at the PLA Hong Kong Garrison on Stonecutters Island. According to Janes data, PLAN's 9th Destroyer Flotilla operates CNS Yan'an while the PLAN's 2nd Destroyer Flotilla operates CNS Zhanjiang and CNS Yuncheng.
properties.label: PLAN's Shandong CSG arrives in Hong Kong
properties.name: PLAN's Shandong CSG arrives in Hong Kong

properties.description: During the United Nations Security Council (UNSC) meeting held to discuss the insecurity in Haiti, the United States, China, and Russia entered a dispute over the nature of the international response to the situation. The US called for a UN peacekeeping mission and strengthening of sanctions. China and Russia expressed their opposition to any expansion of UN-led Multinational Security Support Mission (MSSM). The meeting took place in United States' New York state.
